FACTORY DESIGN PATTERN: 
We seperate object creation and business logic.We only focus on Object creation.
Factory creates an object and gives it to client.

Usually defined in 3 types: 1. Simple Factory -- Kind of design principle.
                            2. Factory Method         --- Design pattern
                            3. Abstract Factory Method --- Design pattern
SIMPLE FACTORY:
Lets say we have Burger as an abstract class and it has 3 types varities. Now creating a burger(object) is what we do.
--Burger and its 3 varities are product but creating burger is done by factory.
We create class of Burger Factory which produces burger. It returns an object called Burger. Now these burger can be of different types.
--Burger factory has a burger.(composition)

FACTORY METHOD:
It defines an interface for creating objects but lets subclasses decide which object to instantiate. It promotes loose coupling by delegating object creation to a method, making the system more flexible and extensible.
--Subclasses override the factory method to create specific object types,enabling flexible object creation.
--Supports easy addition of new product types and improves maintainability and adaptability at runtime.

Example:
Consider a Notification System where you need to send different types of notifications like Email, SMS, or Push notifications. Instead of creating objects directly, you use a Factory Method to decide which notification to create.


ABSTRACT FACTORY METHOD:
The Abstract Factory Pattern is a creational design pattern that provides an interface for creating families of related or dependent objects without specifying their concrete classes. It acts as a "factory of factories," where a super-factory creates other factories that in turn produce specific objects.

Example:
 A UI theme system supports Light and Dark themes, where each theme provides its own set of components like Button and TextBox. The application uses a factory to create these components, allowing it to switch between themes without changing the main code.
 






